                h2 Design process
                p We studied and analyzed Ellen Lupton’s design principles and Chris Ashworth’s design qualities. Then, we created 3 lines of investigation by combining one principle with one quality.
            
            img(src="#", alt="Lines of Investigation")
            p Lines of Investigation

            p We grouped images based on our lines of investigation. This was used to guide our poster creation process for visualizing our art direction.

            img(src="#", alt="Image Grouping")
            p Image Grouping

            p Next we designed and iterated on posters, incorporating the lines of investigation and using different typefaces, color, and image treatment.
            
            img(src="#", alt="Poster Iterations")
            p Poster Iterations

            p As our art direction takes shape, we experimented with the translation of each line to graphic assets.

            img(src="#", alt="Graphic Asset Iterations")
            p Graphic Asset Iterations

            p Once we finalized our art direction,  we started building the microsite. In smaller teams, we worked on content planning, user flow, wireframing, visual design, interaction design, and prototyping.

            img(src="#", alt="User Flow")
            p User Flow

            img(src="#", alt="Landing Page Direction")
            p Landing Page Direction from functional to abstract

            img(src="#", alt="Interaction Design")
